HRM and speed+cadence sensors on the trainer, then power up the GPS when it’s time to head outside. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The ROAM navigation shows on its 2.7-inch, 64-color display. The dual-band GPS is a more accurate navigation device in areas with more obstruction, be it trees or skyscrapers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll get 32 GB of memory to save maps, routes, and workouts.</p>\n\n\n<a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brspreiclearq124&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F195826%2Fwahoo-fitness-elemnt-roam-gps-cycling-computer-bundle\" target=\"_blank\">Shop Now</a>\n\n\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brspreiclearq124&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F182628%2Fcannondale-topstone-carbon-5-bike%3Fcolor%3DGRAPHITE\"><strong>Cannondale Topstone Carbon 5 Bike</strong></a><strong>: $2,620 (20%Off)</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Cannondale-Topstone-Carbon-5-Bike-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This version of the Topstone has a Shimano GRX 800/600 2 x 11-speed drivetrain. It comes with fast 700c x 37 mm tires but has room for 40 mm wide tires, or you can max out flotation with 650b wheels and up to 48 mm wide tires.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Canndondale’s KingPin rear suspension is designed to go hard on dirt and feel smooth on pavement. It allows up to 30 mm of travel at the saddle via a thru-axle pivot where the seat stays and seat tube meet. It has Direct Line internal cable routing, an integrated wheel sensor, fender attachments (including a removable fender bridge), and plenty of mounts for water and bags. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The bike’s geometry positions you slightly upright and forward, with OutFront steering geometry to keep steering nimble while providing stability. For more details, check the full listing at REI. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This model was discontinued in 2023, hence the sale. It’s a great deal on a carbon bike with great components, especially for those getting into gravel. The catch here is that only sizes M and XL are available, and you may want to size up.</p>\n\n\n<a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brspreiclearq124&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F182628%2Fcannondale-topstone-carbon-5-bike%3Fcolor%3DGRAPHITE\" target=\"_blank\">Shop Now</a>\n\n\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brspreiclearq124&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F219009%2Ftrek-commuter-pro-rt-flare-rt-bike-light-set\"><strong>Trek Commuter Pro RT Flare RT Bike Light Set</strong></a><strong>: $160 (23%Off)</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Trek-Commuter-Pro-RT-Flare-RT-Bike-Light-Set-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Trek’s Commuter Pro RT front light with Kindbeam illuminates the ground ahead of you and out of the eyes of anyone ahead of you. The accompanying Flare RT rear light provides visibility on all types of terrain. The front and rear lights can pair wirelessly to control with the push of one button. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Daytime lights have focus, flash, and range flash patterns for daytime visibility for up to 1.2 miles. The Commuter Pro RT modes range from 1,000 lumens to 500 lumens and include a flash mode at 300 lumens that can last 12 hours. Flare RT flash modes: 90 lumens, 6 hrs.; 45 lumens, 12 hrs.; 5 lumens, 15 hrs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Battery life indicators monitor both lights, which can be recharged with the included USB-C and micro-USB cable. </p>\n\n\n<a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293233&amp;ctc=brspreiclearq124&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rei.com%2Fproduct%2F219009%2Ftrek-commuter-pro-rt-flare-rt-bike-light-set\" target=\"_blank\">Shop Now</a>\n\n\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10248&amp;pw=293